edu.um.cps2002.tile_game

Class Player

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.um.cps2002.tile_game.Player

  • public class Player
extends java.lang.Object
    The Player class contains a copy of the game map from the player's perspective, the location of the player on the map, various methods which allow the player to move around the map and a method to generate the HTML code of the player's map.
    Author:
    Luke Collins & Stefania Damato

      • moveAllowed

        public boolean moveAllowed(char move)
        This method examines the player's current position and determines whether or not it is possible to move in a certain direction, ensuring that the player does not move out of the map.
        Parameters:
        move - A direction character, one of u (up), d (down), l (left) or r (right).
        Returns:
        true if the move is admissible, false otherwise.

        public void move(char move)

      • updateMap

        public void updateMap(int x,
                      int y,
                      char type)
               throws java.lang.IllegalStateException
        This function updates the player's copy of the map, effectively 'discovering' new tiles and replacing the ? entries in the playerMapCopy with one of g (grass), w (water), or t (treasure).
        Parameters:
        x - The row of the discovered tile.
        y - The column of the discovered tile.
        type - The discovered tile type, one of g (grass), w (water), or t (treasure).
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - Should the discovered tile already have been discovered and type conflicts with its previous value.

      • generateHTML

        java.lang.String generateHTML(int playerNo)
        This method generates an HTML file for the current player, using the PlayerMap.htmlMapTable(int, int) function to generate an HTML table which represents playerMapCopy.
        Parameters:
        playerNo - Which player this is (player 1, player 2, etc.).
        Returns:
        The HTML file as a String.
